        <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge provides expert guidance on disc stack centrifuge liquid seal break (also called breakover) — one of the most common causes of separation failure in oil purifiers and fuel centrifuges. Liquid seal break occurs when the water seal at the centrifuge bowl periphery is lost, allowing the oil phase to discharge through the water outlet. Dolphin Centrifuge provides troubleshooting support, gravity disc selection, and parts for all Alfa Laval disc centrifuge models. Based in Warren, Michigan, with over 40 years of centrifuge experience.</p>
